<p>Both OneQode and Oracle see gaming as the key first step and are excited to tackle all aspects of a highly connected future together.</p>
<p>“I’m incredibly excited. Oracle has a global footprint and a significant pedigree. They’ve got a proven track record as an excellent partner. We see it as a 1+1=3 moment that allows us to give offerings to customers that they won’t be able to get anywhere else,” said Matt Shearing, OneQode CEO. “Ultimately they [the customers] will be the real winners.”</p>
<p>OneQode is hopeful for further integration into the Oracle ecosystem to provide our industry-leading latency-optimised cloud to enterprise customers for all purposes.</p>
<p>“By leveraging OneQode’s presence in APAC, Oracle will be able to bolster their offering for cross-region solutions,” said Ben Cooper, OneQode Chief Product Officer.</p>
<p>This partnership is part of a strategic push to offer the highest quality enterprise cloud offerings across business use cases, beginning with a focus on gaming before branching into other areas. </p>
<p>“With OneQode’s unique cloud we’ll be able to offer industry-leading latency-optimised solutions to our wide customer base,” says [Oracle spokesperson] “the current level of integration is an exciting first step.”</p>
<h2 class="mt-4">About OneQode</h2>
<p>OneQode is a global infrastructure as a service (IaaS) company operating a latency-optimised international carrier network and <a href="/cloud/">high-performance cloud platform</a> designed for the demands of real-time applications and competitive gaming.</p>
<h2 class="mt-4">About Oracle</h2>
<p>PLDT Global Corporation (PGC), the international arm of the Philippines’ largest integrated telco network PLDT Inc., is a technology services company that provides high-quality communications infrastructure and innovative platforms to its network of carriers, enterprise customers, and distribution partners enabling them to achieve their desired connectivity, reach, and market relevance.</p>